New Features   :
----------------
PETS #39333: in TAP3, add ability to select tap or local currency.
We store the local and tap currency names on the ChargePacket, and the
exchange rate from on to the other.
on output side, we expect all values to be in tap currencies.
new registry entries for tap3:
      #necessary for TAP3 input
      OriginCountryCode		= 0049  # only used for the integRate HEADER
      SenderCountryCode		= 0049  # only used for the integRate HEADER
      UseLocalCurrency		= FALSE # store tap amounts by default
      #necessary for TAP3 output
      TapCurrency		= SDR # used as default when not found on EDR
      TapDecimalPlaces		= 3   # ie 13.21 is stored as 13210
      ExchangeRateDecimalPlaces	= 3   # ie 13.21 is stored as 13210
      NetworkType		= 0   # 0=Mixed/1=Terrestrial/2=Satellite

